MongoDB queries

1. Find all the information about each products
  ANS: db.guvi_products.find()

2. Find the product price which are between 400 to 800
  ANS: db.guvi_products.find({ product_price: { $gte: 400, $lte: 800 } })

3. Find the product price which are not between 400 to 600
  ANS: db.guvi_products.find({ product_price: { $not: { $gt: 400, $lt: 600 } } })

4. List the four product which are greater than 500 in price 
  ANS: db.guvi_products.find({ product_price: { $gt: 500 } })

5. Find the product name and product material of each products
  ANS: db.guvi_products.find({}, { product_name: 1, product_material: 1, _id: 0 })

6. Find the product with a row id of 10
  ANS: db.guvi_products.findOne({ id: "10" })

7. Find only the product name and product material
  ANS: db.guvi_products.find({}, { product_name: 1, product_material: 1, _id: 0 })

8. Find all products which contain the value of soft in product material 
  ANS: db.guvi_products.find({ product_material: { $regex: /soft/i } }).pretty()

9. Find products which contain product color indigo  and product price 492.00
  ANS: db.guvi_products.find({ $or: [ { product_color: "indigo" }, { product_price: 492.00 }]})

10. Delete the products which product price value are 28
  ANS: db.guvi_products.deleteMany({ product_price: 28 })
